<paragraph id="8BEDE437FFDA3D02FF59FEC8EF2A628F" blockId="8.[151,1437,151,1007]" pageId="8" pageNumber="252">
<emphasis id="B9263825FFDA3D02FF59FEC8EA4C6117" bold="true" box="[199,349,262,287]" pageId="8" pageNumber="252">Recognition.</emphasis>
In the keys to the males of the British species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C529FB4FFDA3D02FC08FEC8EFAA6117" authority="Disney, 1989" authorityName="Disney" authorityYear="1989" box="[918,1211,262,287]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="252" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9263825FFDA3D02FC08FEC8EF1A6117" box="[918,1035,262,287]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="252">Megaselia</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFC399C6FFDA3D02FB85FEC8EFA26117" author="Disney" box="[1051,1203,262,287]" pageId="8" pageNumber="252" refString="Disney, R. H. L. (1989) Scuttle flies. Diptera, Phoridae, genus Megaselia. Handbooks for the Identification of British Insects, 10 (8), 1 - 155." type="journal article" year="1989">
Disney, 
<number id="3D9AF610FFDA3D02FBE4FEC9EFA26117" box="[1146,1203,263,287]" pageId="8" pageNumber="252" value="1989.0">1989</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
this species runs to couplet 
<number id="3D9AF610FFDA3D02FF6FFEE4EA1E614B" box="[241,271,298,323]" pageId="8" pageNumber="252" value="68.0">68</number>
, where neither option applies, although 
<taxonomicName id="4C529FB4FFDA3D02FD4AFEE2E8AC614B" authority="Loew" authorityName="Loew" box="[724,957,299,323]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="252" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigriceps">
<emphasis id="B9263825FFDA3D02FD4AFEE2E873614B" box="[724,866,300,323]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="252">M. nigriceps</emphasis>
(Loew)
</taxonomicName>
is close to new species, both with inflated palps with short bristles but they differ in the shape; they also differ in the hypopygium (especially in the shape of epandrium and length of anal tube) and by having, the new species, the hairs below basal half of femur shorter than 
<taxonomicName id="4C529FB4FFDA3D02FF09FE56EA9561A7" authority="Loew" authorityName="Loew" box="[151,388,407,431]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="252" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigriceps">
<emphasis id="B9263825FFDA3D02FF09FE56EA3461A7" box="[151,293,408,431]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="252">M. nigriceps</emphasis>
(Loew)
</taxonomicName>
. The subsequently added 
<taxonomicName id="4C529FB4FFDA3D02FD34FE56E89761A7" authority="Schmitz" authorityName="Schmitz" box="[682,902,406,431]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="252" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="funesta">
<emphasis id="B9263825FFDA3D02FD34FE56E83061A7" box="[682,801,407,431]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="252">M. funesta</emphasis>
Schmitz
</taxonomicName>
runs to the same point; it differs from the new species in the hypopygium (shape of epandrium and length of anal tube), and in the shape of inflated palps (wider in the new species). The related species 
<taxonomicName id="4C529FB4FFDA3D02FDC5FE2EE85161FF" authority="Wood" authorityName="Wood" box="[603,832,478,503]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="252" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simulans">
<emphasis id="B9263825FFDA3D02FDC5FE2EE9F461FF" box="[603,741,478,503]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="252">M. simulans</emphasis>
(Wood)
</taxonomicName>
has a similar hypopygium to the new species, but the palps of 
<taxonomicName id="4C529FB4FFDA3D02FE9EFDCAEAFD6213" authority="Wood" authorityName="Wood" box="[256,492,514,539]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="252" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simulans">
<emphasis id="B9263825FFDA3D02FE9EFDCAEA9C6213" box="[256,397,514,539]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="252">M. simulans</emphasis>
(Wood)
</taxonomicName>
are smaller and with longer bristles (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC399C6FFDA3D02FC35FDCCEF476213" author="Disney" box="[939,1110,514,539]" pageId="8" pageNumber="252" refString="Disney, R. H. L. (2011 b) Megaselia nigriceps (Loew) variety funesta Schmitz (Diptera: Phoridae) now recognised as a distinct species. Entomologist's Monthly Magazine, 62, 277 - 281." type="journal article" year="2011" yearSuffix="b">
Disney, 
<number id="3D9AF610FFDA3D02FB92FDCCEF566213" box="[1036,1095,514,539]" pageId="8" pageNumber="252" value="2011.0">2011</number>
b
</bibRefCitation>
). The species 
<taxonomicName id="4C529FB4FFDA3D02FB61FDCAEBE76237" authority="Schmitz" authorityName="Schmitz" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="252" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="specularis">
<emphasis id="B9263825FFDA3D02FB61FDCAEE8A6213" box="[1279,1435,514,539]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="252">M. specularis</emphasis>
Schmitz
</taxonomicName>
, with a similar hypopygium to the new species, it differs in shape of epandrium and palps (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC399C6FFDA3D02FAB5FDE8EA26626B" author="Disney" pageId="8" pageNumber="252" refString="Disney, R. H. L. &amp; Durska, E. (2011) Five new species and three new records of Megaselia Rondani (Diptera: Phoridae) from Pisz forest (Poland). Annales Zoologici, 61 (3), 527 - 534. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.3161 / 000345411 x 603373" type="journal article" year="2011">
Disney &amp; Durska, 
<number id="3D9AF610FFDA3D02FF65FD85EA26626B" box="[251,311,587,611]" pageId="8" pageNumber="252" value="2011.0">2011</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). In the keys of Palaearctic 
<taxonomicName id="4C529FB4FFDA3D02FD13FD84E9E0626B" box="[653,753,586,611]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="252" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Phoridae</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFC399C6FFDA3D02FC9AFD84E8E0626B" author="Schmitz" box="[772,1009,586,611]" pageId="8" pageNumber="252" refString="Schmitz, H., Beyer, H. y. &amp; Delage, A. (1938 - 1981) Phoridae. In: Lindner, E. (Ed.), Die Fliegen der palaearktischen Region, 4 (33), pp. 1 - 712. [Stuttgart]" type="journal article" year="1938">
Schmitz 
<emphasis id="B9263825FFDA3D02FCF0FD82E8BB626B" box="[878,938,586,611]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="252">et al,</emphasis>
<date id="FFECC2F7FFDA3D02FC26FD85E8E0626B" box="[952,1009,587,611]" pageId="8" pageNumber="252" value="1938" valueMax="1981">
<number id="3D9AF610FFDA3D02FC26FD85E8E0626B" box="[952,1009,587,611]" pageId="8" pageNumber="252" value="1938.0">1938</number>
</date>
</bibRefCitation>
– 
<number id="3D9AF610FFDA3D02FB9FFD85EF0A626B" box="[1025,1051,587,611]" pageId="8" pageNumber="252" value="81.0">81</number>
) this species runs to couplet 
<number id="3D9AF610FFDA3D02FA1EFD85EE8D626B" box="[1408,1436,587,611]" pageId="8" pageNumber="252" value="22.0">22</number>
(Abteilung I, page 
<number id="3D9AF610FFDA3D02FEF4FDA1EA89628F" box="[362,408,623,647]" pageId="8" pageNumber="252" value="407.0">407</number>
), to 
<taxonomicName id="4C529FB4FFDA3D02FE56FDBEE9A7628F" authority="Becker" authorityName="Becker" box="[456,694,622,647]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="252" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="projecta">
<emphasis id="B9263825FFDA3D02FE56FDBEE95B628F" box="[456,586,624,647]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="252">M. projecta</emphasis>
(Becker)
</taxonomicName>
, synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C529FB4FFDA3D02FCD3FDBEEF26628F" authority="Loew" authorityName="Loew" box="[845,1079,623,647]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="252" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigriceps">
<emphasis id="B9263825FFDA3D02FCD3FDBEE8CB628F" box="[845,986,624,647]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="252">M. nigriceps</emphasis>
(Loew)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
